---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QuickSummary from '../components/QuickSummary.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Squad Building" 
  description="Main Squad First philosophy, UR hero focus, Tank squad strategy for mid-game players, Monica for Doomed Elites, and practical mono-type builds for Last War: Survival."
>
  <h1>Squad Building</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-[#8a96b0]">This is the single most important section on the entire site. Everything else is secondary until your main squad is strong.</p>

  <QuickSummary title="The Golden Rule — Main Squad First">
    <p><strong>Put 70-80% of your resources into one squad.</strong></p>
    <p>A dominant #1 squad carries you through the vast majority of content (Alliance events, Doomed Elites, most PvE, decent Arena). Your 2nd and 3rd squads only need to be "good enough" to clean up the rest.</p>
    <p class="mt-2">Spreading shards, gear, and research evenly across multiple squads is the #1 reason mid-game players feel stuck.</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>Squad Fundamentals</h2>
  
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-base">Core Rules</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li><strong>5 heroes per squad</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Mono-type only</strong> (all Tank / all Aircraft / all Missile). The type bonus is massive — mixing types is almost always a mistake in mid-game.</li>
        <li><strong>Positioning matters</strong>. Frontline tanks draw fire. Backline DPS focuses the same target.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-base">Formation (Visual)</h3>
      <div class="bg-[#111a2e] p-4 rounded border border-[#2a3854]">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 320 180" class="w-full max-w-[280px] mx-auto" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <!-- Background grid -->
          <rect x="20" y="20" width="280" height="140" rx="4" fill="#1a253f" stroke="#3a4966"/>
          
          <!-- Front row label -->
          <text x="30" y="45" fill="#8a96b0" font-size="10">FRONT (Draws fire)</text>
          
          <!-- Front Left -->
          <rect x="50" y="55" width="70" height="45" rx="4" fill="#1e3a5f" stroke="#3b82f6" stroke-width="2"/>
          <text x="85" y="78" fill="#93c5fd" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="600">Main Tank</text>
          <text x="85" y="92" fill="#64748b" font-size="9" text-anchor="middle">Williams / Murphy</text>
          
          <!-- Front Right -->
          <rect x="140" y="55" width="70" height="45" rx="4" fill="#1e3a5f" stroke="#3b82f6" stroke-width="2"/>
          <text x="175" y="78" fill="#93c5fd" font-size="11" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="600">Support Tank</text>
          <text x="175" y="92" fill="#64748b" font-size="9" text-anchor="middle">Murphy / Lucius</text>
          
          <!-- Back row label -->
          <text x="30" y="120" fill="#8a96b0" font-size="10">BACK (DPS focus fire)</text>
          
          <!-- Back Left (Primary DPS) -->
          <rect x="50" y="130" width="70" height="35" rx="4" fill="#3f2a00" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="2"/>
          <text x="85" y="148" fill="#fcd34d" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="600">Primary DPS</text>
          <text x="85" y="160" fill="#64748b" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle">Kim / Scarlett</text>
          
          <!-- Back Center -->
          <rect x="140" y="130" width="70" height="35" rx="4" fill="#3f2a00" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="2"/>
          <text x="175" y="148" fill="#fcd34d" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="600">Strong DPS</text>
          <text x="175" y="160" fill="#64748b" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle">Stetmann</text>
          
          <!-- Back Right -->
          <rect x="230" y="130" width="70" height="35" rx="4" fill="#2a1f4d" stroke="#a78bfa" stroke-width="2"/>
          <text x="265" y="148" fill="#c4b5fd" font-size="10" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="600">Support</text>
          <text x="265" y="160" fill="#64748b" font-size="8" text-anchor="middle">Marshall / Adam</text>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <p class="text-[10px] text-[#5e6b85] text-center mt-1">Adjust slightly based on matchup. Murphy is excellent vs Missile.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>The Tank Squad Exception (Very Common in Mid-Game)</h2>
  <p>Many strong mid-game players (especially F2P/low spenders) run <strong>two full Tank squads</strong> before seriously building Aircraft or Missile.</p>
  
  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Why Two Tanks Works Well</th><th>When to Finally Diversify</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="text-sm">Tank is the most forgiving type for PvE, gathering, defense, and many Alliance events.</td>
          <td class="text-sm">Your main Tank squad has core heroes at 4–5★ with good gear/skills and you're consistently top 50-100 on your server in relevant content.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="text-sm">You only need one strong counter squad later. Two solid Tanks let you handle most content while you slowly build the counter type.</td>
          <td class="text-sm">Your server meta is heavily skewed toward one type and you're losing important fights because of type disadvantage.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>UR Focus vs Realistic Mid-Game Progression</h2>
  <p>UR heroes are the correct long-term investment. Their power curve is noticeably higher once starred and geared.</p>
  <p>However, <strong>well-built SSR heroes (especially season promotables)</strong> are perfectly viable for most mid-game content. Mason, Scarlett, Violet, Sarah, and Venom have all been strong promotable options in different seasons.</p>

  <QuickSummary title="Transition Rule">
    <p>Keep your highest-starred SSR/promotable heroes in your main squad until you have a UR replacement at comparable or better investment. Never bench a 5★ SSR for a 1–2★ UR just because it's "UR".</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>Monica — Your Elite Farming Machine</h2>
  <div class="quick-summary">
    <p><strong>Put Monica in your Doomed Elite squads</strong> (lead the rally or just join as a member — the bonus applies either way).</p>
    <p class="mt-1">Her skill gives a very strong resource multiplier on elites and regular zombies. Community testing shows roughly +30% at low investment up to +70%+ when reasonably skilled.</p>
    <p class="mt-1"><strong>Sweet spot investment:</strong> 3–4 stars + skill level 8–12 is usually enough. Do not take resources away from your main combat DPS/tanks to max her.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Recommended Mid-Game Priority Order</h2>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-1 text-sm">
    <li><strong>Stars on your top 3–4 heroes</strong> in the main squad (especially your primary DPS like Kim)</li>
    <li><strong>Gear</strong> on those same heroes (Mythic/Legendary pieces first on DPS, then defensive pieces on tanks)</li>
    <li><strong>Skills</strong> — max active skills on your main DPS before dumping everything into passives</li>
    <li><strong>Exclusive weapons</strong> when available for your core heroes</li>
    <li>Only then start heavily investing a second squad</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Practical Mid-Game Example Builds</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">These are directionally strong for many servers in 2026. Always adapt to what you actually have at high stars.</p>

  <h3 class="text-base mt-6">Strong Tank Squad (Mid-Game)</h3>
  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Position</th><th>Hero</th><th>Priority Notes</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Front Left</td><td>Williams (or Murphy)</td><td>Highest durability tank you have</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Front Right</td><td>Murphy / Lucius</td><td>Good vs Missile, solid support</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Back Left (Main DPS)</td><td>Kimberly (Kim)</td><td><strong>Highest priority</strong> — push stars + gear + exclusive weapon hard</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Back Center</td><td>Stetmann</td><td>Excellent all-rounder, great in many lineups</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Back Right</td><td>Marshall / Adam / Scarlett</td><td>Flex slot — use your best remaining starred hero</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h3 class="text-base mt-6">Example Second Squad (When Ready)</h3>
  <p class="text-sm">Many players make their second squad another Tank until they have enough resources for a proper Aircraft or Missile squad that can actually compete.</p>

  <h2>When (and How) to Start Your Second Type</h2>
  <p>Do not start spreading resources until your main squad is "good enough" for the content that matters to you.</p>
  <p class="text-sm mt-2">Good signals you're ready to diversify:</p>
  <ul class="text-sm list-disc pl-5">
    <li>Your main squad is 4–5★ on core heroes with decent Mythic gear</li>
    <li>You're consistently clearing the Alliance events and Doomed Elites you care about</li>
    <li>You have a decent surplus of universal shards and skill medals</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mt-8 p-4 bg-[#1a253f] border border-[#f59e0b]/30 rounded">
    <p class="text-sm"><strong>Final reminder:</strong> One cracked squad beats three average squads 95% of the time in mid-game. Protect your main squad's resources like they're gold — because for the next few months, they are.</p>
  </div>
</Layout>